Package main.java.models

Class Ticket

java.lang.Object
main.java.models.Ticket
public class Ticket extends Object
Represents a transaction ticket for car purchases or returns in a dealership system. This class holds detailed information about the transaction including the car involved and the financial details.

    • Ticket

      public Ticket(int ticketId, String userFirstName, String userLastName, String username, String carId, String purchasedCarModel, String carType, int carYear, double originalPrice, double finalPrice, Date purchaseDate, boolean isReturn)
      Constructs a new Ticket instance with all required details.
      Parameters:
      ticketId - The unique identifier for the ticket.
      userFirstName - The first name of the user associated with the ticket.
      userLastName - The last name of the user associated with the ticket.
      username - The username of the user associated with the ticket.
      carId - The unique identifier for the car involved in the transaction.
      purchasedCarModel - The model of the car purchased or returned.
      carType - The type of the car involved in the transaction.
      carYear - The manufacture year of the car.
      originalPrice - The original price of the car before any adjustments.
      finalPrice - The final price of the car after adjustments.
      purchaseDate - The date when the transaction occurred.
      isReturn - Indicates whether the ticket represents a return (true) or a purchase (false).
